          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <categoryLinks>
        <categoryLink targetId="629c-c441-50b1-a5c9" id="02d1-3f73-9f5b-857c" primary="true" name="Configuration"/>
      </categoryLinks>
    </selectionEntry>
    <selectionEntry type="upgrade" import="true" name="Faction Rule: Issue orders" hidden="false" id="87f6-4a2f-b7da-ade3" sortIndex="1">
      <rules>
        <rule name="Issue Orders" id="9879-6fbc-0432-18cd" hidden="false">
          <description>If you have selected Hegemonic Order as your faction, then officer models you control may choose to issue orders during their turn. To do so, the officer must give a order (see the orders reference) to a friendly unit within 9&quot; of the officer, officers may order themselves/their own unit if they are the correct type of unit for the order. Each order lasts until the start of the next round. Each unit can only be effected by 1 order at a time. If a unit is under the effect a order and is ordered again, the new order overrides the old one.</description>
        </rule>
      </rules>
      <categoryLinks>
        <categoryLink targetId="629c-c441-50b1-a5c9" id="be93-e743-5ad2-00e3" primary="true" name="Configuration"/>
      </categoryLinks>
    </selectionEntry>
  </selectionEntries>
