  <sharedSelectionEntryGroups>
    <selectionEntryGroup name="Regiment" id="b3c6-1e45-b005-9bc2" hidden="false">
      <selectionEntries>
        <selectionEntry type="upgrade" import="true" name="Battlegroup Seven" hidden="false" id="6d10-9191-a318-9c74">
          <rules>
            <rule name="Battlegroup Seven" id="c99b-79ac-9404-1571" hidden="true">
              <comment>With lore</comment>
              <description>*The Elite of the Elites in the hegemonic order, deployed to the front lines and defending command Structures during sieges, the Battlegroup Seven infantry are a gold standard for all regiments.*

When you have Battlegroup Seven Selected as your regiment, all units in your army gain the following

**Parade Firing line:** If all models in a infantry unit in your army are in contract with atleast 1 other model in that unit, every model in that unit adds 1 to their hit rolls when making ranged attacks

**Only the Best:** Your army cannot have Conscript units</description>
              <modifiers>
                <modifier type="set" value="false" field="hidden">
                  <conditions>
                    <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="force" childId="8b56-1ed1-7f7d-2738" shared="true" includeChildSelections="true"/>
                  </conditions>
                </modifier>
              </modifiers>
            </rule>
            <rule name="Battlegroup Seven" id="0ba1-66f1-4db1-ab58" hidden="false">
              <comment>Without lore</comment>
              <description>When you have Battlegroup Seven Selected as your regiment, all units in your army gain the following

**Parade Firing line:** If all models in a infantry unit in your army are in contract with atleast 1 other model in that unit, every model in that unit adds 1 to their hit rolls when making ranged attacks

**Only the Best:** Your army cannot have Conscript units</description>
              <modifiers>
                <modifier type="set" value="true" field="hidden">
                  <conditions>
                    <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="force" childId="8b56-1ed1-7f7d-2738" shared="true" includeChildSelections="true"/>
                  </conditions>
                </modifier>
              </modifiers>
            </rule>
          </rules>
        </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry type="upgrade" import="true" name="H.V.A.D Corps" hidden="false" id="4fef-936c-67d4-aae0">
          <rules>
            <rule name="H.V.A.D Corps" id="51e7-031c-e094-560e" hidden="true">
              <modifiers>
                <modifier type="set" value="false" field="hidden">
                  <conditions>
                    <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="force" childId="8b56-1ed1-7f7d-2738" shared="true" includeChildSelections="true"/>
                  </conditions>
                </modifier>
              </modifiers>
              <description>*The High Velocity Air Drop Corps form the elite of the Hegemonic Order’s Air Deployed Infantry, while this does have some advantages, their high Ego can make certain battlefield operations difficult.*

When you have H.V.A.D Corps Selected as your regiment, all units in your army gain the following

Short Range Elimination: When Firing a weapon at a enemy unit within half range of the attacking model, that weapon gains Sustained 1.

Itchy Trigger Finger: When this unit fires, it must fire at the closet Visible enemy</description>
              <comment>With lore</comment>
            </rule>
            <rule name="H.V.A.D Corps" id="5d9d-a191-ef4c-cd6d" hidden="false">
              <comment>Without lore</comment>
              <description>When you have H.V.A.D Corps Selected as your regiment, all units in your army gain the following

Short Range Elimination: When Firing a weapon at a enemy unit within half range of the attacking model, that weapon gains Sustained 1.

Itchy Trigger Finger: When this unit fires, it must fire at the closet Visible enemy</description>
              <modifiers>
                <modifier type="set" value="true" field="hidden">
                  <conditions>
                    <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="force" childId="8b56-1ed1-7f7d-2738" shared="true" includeChildSelections="true"/>
                  </conditions>
                </modifier>
              </modifiers>
            </rule>
          </rules>
        </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry type="upgrade" import="true" name="Last Chancers" hidden="false" id="b53d-33a2-df4e-c527">
          <rules>
            <rule name="Last Chancers" id="61d9-e92e-7211-7c68" hidden="true">
              <comment>With Lore</comment>
              <description>*Constructed of Conscripts and prisoners, so called “Last Chance” regiments are deployed under armed poorly supplied to hellish combat scenarios.*

When you have Last Chancers Selected as your regiment, all units in your army gain the following

**Self Preservation instincts**: When a Last Chancers unit is selected as the target of attacks, if that unit has less than its starting number of models, that unit gains +1 to its save

**Look out Commandant!**: For each Field Commandant model in your army, roll 1d10 before the game starts, on each roll of 1 that Field Commandant has a unfortunate accident and is removed from play before the game begins.</description>
              <modifiers>
                <modifier type="set" value="false" field="hidden">
                  <conditions>
                    <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="force" childId="8b56-1ed1-7f7d-2738" shared="true" includeChildSelections="true"/>
                  </conditions>
                </modifier>
              </modifiers>
            </rule>
            <rule name="Last Chancers" id="2eb9-7127-e08d-bd63" hidden="false">
              <comment>Without Lore</comment>
              <description>When you have Last Chancers Selected as your regiment, all units in your army gain the following

**Self Preservation instincts**: When a Last Chancers unit is selected as the target of attacks, if that unit has less than its starting number of models, that unit gains +1 to its save

**Look out Commandant!**: For each Field Commandant model in your army, roll 1d10 before the game starts, on each roll of 1 that Field Commandant has a unfortunate accident and is removed from play before the game begins.</description>
              <modifiers>
                <modifier type="set" value="true" field="hidden">
                  <conditions>
                    <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="force" childId="8b56-1ed1-7f7d-2738" shared="true" includeChildSelections="true"/>
                  </conditions>
                </modifier>
              </modifiers>
            </rule>
          </rules>
        </selectionEntry>
